# AGENTS.md — layout spec for AI coding agents

This project was scaffolded by [project-init]({{project_init_url}}) and follows a model-agnostic layout so that any coding agent (Claude Code, Cursor, Aider, Codex, Gemini, etc.) can navigate it.

## Where things live

```
.
├── CLAUDE.md             # Claude Code entry point (thin — redirects here)
├── AGENTS.md             # this file
└── .claude/
    ├── project-init.md   # project workflow and conventions
    ├── config.yaml       # tools/MCPs selected at init
    ├── settings.json     # Claude Code settings (safe for other agents to ignore)
    ├── memory/
    │   ├── MEMORY.md     # index of memory files — READ FIRST for context
    │   └── *.md          # small structured memory files (user/feedback/project/reference)
    ├── vault/            # Obsidian vault — human-authored docs
    │   ├── decisions/    # architectural decisions (ADRs)
    │   ├── design/       # design notes
    │   ├── sessions/     # session logs
    │   └── knowledge/    # domain notes
    ├── commands/         # Claude Code slash commands (markdown)
    ├── skills/           # Claude Code skills (markdown)
    ├── agents/           # Claude Code subagents (markdown)
    ├── hooks/            # deterministic session hooks (bash/python)
    └── scripts/          # helper scripts (bash/python)
```

## Orientation protocol (all agents)

When starting work on this project:

1. Read [`.claude/project-init.md`](.claude/project-init.md) for the workflow and conventions.
2. Read [`.claude/memory/MEMORY.md`](.claude/memory/MEMORY.md) to load prior context.
3. Browse [`.claude/vault/`](.claude/vault/) for design/decision notes relevant to your task.
4. Check [`.claude/config.yaml`](.claude/config.yaml) to see which MCPs/tools are installed.

## Memory conventions

Memory files in `.claude/memory/` use a simple frontmatter schema:

```markdown
---
name: <short title>
description: <one-line summary used for relevance ranking>
type: user | feedback | project | reference
---

<body>
```

`MEMORY.md` is a plain index — one bullet per memory file, under ~150 chars per line.

See [`.claude/memory/README.md`](.claude/memory/README.md) for the full convention.

## Per-agent notes

- **Claude Code**: `.claude/` is native. `CLAUDE.md` at root is auto-loaded.
- **Cursor**: create `.cursorrules` with `"Read AGENTS.md and .claude/project-init.md before starting any task."`
- **Aider**: add to `.aider.conf.yml` → `read: [AGENTS.md, .claude/project-init.md]`
- **Codex / other**: point the agent at `AGENTS.md` first.

## Deterministic-first principle

Hooks and scripts in `.claude/` prefer bash/python over LLM calls. Reserve LLM calls for genuinely generative tasks (summarization, entity extraction, judgment). Everything else — file ops, pattern matching, template rendering, graph traversal — is deterministic code.
